column5: Where is an inexpensive Long Point Bay launch?
I think old cut is the cheapest @ 10.00 the Provincial Park is 10.75 the rest I've been to are 15 to 20
That does it. I'm building a few ramps.
just before the entrance to the long point provincial park entrance  - take old cut blvd north off of erie blvd, then right on roger's ave     http://www.oldcut.com/services.htm
Albert you will also see a small marine shop on rogers ave on the right. The ramp is right there beside it. There is also another one further down the rd.

The one at the shop is Post Marine thats where I like to Launch but I havn't been to the park yet but I want to get a season pass for the park Post Marine allows for Power on if your doing that kind of thing
